<hr data-start="140" data-end="143">
<h3 data-start="145" data-end="197">✅ 1. <strong data-start="154" data-end="197">Backup PHP Files (Source Code + Assets)</strong></h3>
<p data-start="199" data-end="254">You can do this manually or automatically via a script.</p>
<h4 data-start="256" data-end="304"><strong data-start="261" data-end="304">Manual Method (via File Manager or FTP)</strong></h4>
<ol data-start="305" data-end="505">
<li data-start="305" data-end="368">
<p data-start="308" data-end="368">Connect to your server via FTP or your hosting file manager.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="369" data-end="456">
<p data-start="372" data-end="456">Download the entire project folder (usually in <code data-start="419" data-end="432">public_html</code>, <code data-start="434" data-end="442">htdocs</code>, or similar).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="457" data-end="505">
<p data-start="460" data-end="505">Compress it to a <code data-start="477" data-end="483">.zip</code> file for safekeeping.</p>
</li>
</ol>
