<h3 data-start="1683" data-end="1735">✅ 3. <strong data-start="1692" data-end="1735">(Optional) Combine Both into One Script</strong></h3>
<p data-start="1737" data-end="1801">You can automate both steps using a cron job or PHP script that:</p>
<ul data-start="1802" data-end="1871">
<li data-start="1802" data-end="1832">
<p data-start="1804" data-end="1832">Dumps the database to <code data-start="1826" data-end="1832">.sql</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start="1833" data-end="1871">
<p data-start="1835" data-end="1871">Zips all project files + <code data-start="1860" data-end="1866">.sql</code> file</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start="1873" data-end="1935">Let me know if you'd like this full automation script as well.</p>
<hr data-start="1937" data-end="1940">
<h3 data-start="1942" data-end="1964">🔒 Tips for Safety</h3>
<ul data-start="1965" data-end="2170">
<li data-start="1965" data-end="2031">
<p data-start="1967" data-end="2031">Store backups <strong data-start="1981" data-end="1992">offsite</strong> (Google Drive, Dropbox, external HDD).</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2032" data-end="2103">
<p data-start="2034" data-end="2103"><strong data-start="2034" data-end="2070">Automate daily or weekly backups</strong> if your system is in production.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="2104" data-end="2170">
<p data-start="2106" data-end="2170">Always <strong data-start="2113" data-end="2134">test your backups</strong> by restoring them on a test server.</p>
</li>
</ul>
